    <body>
        <div xml:id="KT195-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">piriviṭaip paruva varaviṉkaṇ kiḻatti melintu kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Spoken by HER, becoming weak at the coming of the season in the time of separation.</p>
          </div>
          

        <div xml:id="KT195">
            <lg type="edition">
<l>                cuṭarciṉan taṇintu kuṉṟañ cērap</l>
<l>                paṭarcuman teḻutaru paiyuṇ mālai</l>
<l>                yāṇṭuḷar kollō vēṇṭuviṉai muṭina</l>
<l>                riṉṉā tiraṅku meṉṉā raṉṉō</l>
<l>                taivara lacaivaḷi meypāyn tuṟutarac</l>
<l>                ceyvuṟu pāvai yaṉṉaveṉ</l>
<l>                meypiṟi tākuta laṟiyā tōrē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
              <l>Where is he,</l>
              <l rend="indent">in sorrowful evening that comes upon<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">eḻu taru</term>: here <term xml:lang="ta">taru-tal</term> as an auxiliary, namely the evening which comes up irresistibly.</note> [me] laden with affliction,</l>
              <l rend="indent">as the [sun's] glowing anger subsides [and] joins the hills,</l>
              <l>he who didn't know my body would become different<note place="foot">For parallels to <term xml:lang="ta">ākutal</term> as "that" see KT 4.4, 360.2, 386.6.</note>,</l>
              <l rend="indent">– as if a doll that acts<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">ceyvu uṟu pāvai</term>: <term xml:lang="ta">uṟu</term> is best understood here as a mere verbaliser; the nuance distinguishing this from a plain verbal root might be something like "a doll having the faculty of action".</note>,</l>
              <l rend="indent">when the abrasive, moving wind<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">acai vaḷi</term>: "wind which moves [permanently]"?</note> assails<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">mey pāyntu uṟu tara</term>?! Without <term xml:lang="ta">uṟu</term> this would be: "to start abruptly" (= Srin.'s "assail").</note> [her] body, -</l>
              <l>he who, alas, didn't say that it sounds unsweet</l>
              <l rend="indent3">that he had to complete work?</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
